{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875450665,"sessionID":"ses_285934c83fferBWbvWbvpX0uq6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6ce0b3001VNnLxlbN8w7Yn2","messageID":"msg_d7a6cd5ec001wW4CvrU8Gf1X9H","sessionID":"ses_285934c83fferBWbvWbvpX0uq6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_57e1f13a8a754cbd967f80b9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","limit":30},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, consolidating from multiple separate Dockerfiles into 3 optimized container images: `agentcube-router`, `agentcube-workload-manager`, and `agentcube-agentd` (with `picod` sidecar option).\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: AgentCube currently lacks a unified Docker build strategy for its server-side Go binaries. The project has 4 binaries that need to be containerized:\n12: - `router` — HTTP traffic router with session management\n13: - `workload-manager` — Sandbox orchestration controller\n14: - `agentd` — Idle cleanup controller\n15: - `picod` — Daemon for sandbox pods (sidecar pattern)\n16: \n17: Without multi-stage builds, each component requires separate build contexts, large base images, and manual artifact management. This increases CI/CD complexity and image size.\n18: \n19: ### Goal\n20: \n21: Create consolidated Dockerfiles using multi-stage builds at `docker/`:\n22: - Consolidate build artifacts into minimal runtime images\n23: - Reduce image size by ~60-70% compared to single-stage builds\n24: - Use distroless or Alpine base images for production\n25: - Support both development (with debugging tools) and production builds\n26: \n27: ### Value\n28: \n29: - **Image Size**: Smaller images (~50-100MB vs ~300MB+)\n30: - **Security**: Fewer packages in runtime image = smaller attack surface\n\n(Showing lines 1-30 of 267. Use offset=31 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, consolidating from multiple separate Dockerfiles into 3 optimized container images: `agentcube-router`, `agentcube-workload-manager`, and `agentcube-agentd` (with `picod` sidecar option).\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube currently lacks a unified Docker build strategy for its server-side Go binaries. The project has 4 binaries that need to be containerized:\n- `router` — HTTP traffic router with session management\n- `workload-manager` — Sandbox orchestration controller\n- `agentd` — Idle cleanup controller\n- `picod` — Daemon for sandbox pods (sidecar pattern)\n\nWithout multi-stage builds, each component requires separate build contexts, large base images, and manual artifact management. This increases CI/CD complexity and image size.\n\n### Goal\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775875450654,"end":1775875450663}}}}
